The paper discusses the challenge of planning and scheduling for autonomous planetary vehicles, which involves complex hybrid systems with nonlinear dynamics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions safety constraints, which indicates that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of model checking for planning suggests that the paper may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a planning tool, which suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
